Edition:
Quote: (Queen Charlotte Sound) With hook and line we caught chiefly a blackish fish of the size of a hadock, call'd Cole fish by the seamen [ed. fn Blue Cod, <i>Parapercis colias</i>.] but differing much from that known by the same name in Europe, ...
Notes: 1777 Feb Anderson's Journal in Cook Journals (1967) 3/807

Date: 0/0/1777
Source: Voyage Round the World
Author: FORSTER
Vol / Page: 1/126
Edition:
Quote: The best and most savoury fish was a species of cod, which, from its external colour, our sailors called a coal-fish : besides this we caught several species of excellent flat cavalhas (<i>sciaenae</i>), some scorpens, mullets, horse-mackrel, and many other sorts ... which were entirely unknown in Europe
