Date: 19/11/1793
Source: Letter
Author:
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote: Fresh provisions are readily procured [at Dusky Sound]. Coal-fish are innumerable, and may be caught with hooks and lines in almost any quantity, and have this peculiar excellence - my people ate them without bread for many months twice a day, and [179] were fond of them to the last.
Notes: 1793 Nov 19 Capt. Raven to Lieut-Governor King in 1908 McNab Historical Records 1/178-179

