Edition:
Quote: There are also several other kinds of fish, which are called by the sailors, from some slight resemblance to the English sorts, <i>Herrings, Horse-mackarel, Cole-fish</i>, and <i>Ling.</i> The latter is often taken of the weight of forty pounds.
