Notes:

Date: 0/0/1957
Source: Sea Anglers' Fishes of NZ
Author: PARROTT
Vol / Page: 169
Edition:
Quote: Blue Cod Parapercichthys colias Coal-fish <i>Ibid.</i> 141 This [Blue Cod], is the fish known to Captain Cook as the `Coal-fish', and it has frequently been referred to by older authors as the `Rock Cod'. It was known to the Maoris as `Rawaru' or `Pakirikiri'.
Notes:

